# 🌿 English Contemplation

Acharya Shri Jayaprakash Pandey Ji has beautifully unfolded one of Vedānta's most sublime truths.

The vision of God evolves—not because God changes, but because our understanding deepens.

At first, we worship the Divine in sacred forms:

the Guru,

the parents,

the chosen Deity.

Then, through Self-knowledge,

we discover that the very Consciousness shining within is none other than the Supreme Self.

Finally,

the last veil falls.

The entire universe is recognized as the living expression of the One Reality.

This is the meaning of:

> **"वासुदेवः सर्वमिति"**
> *"All this is truly Vāsudeva."*

Then nothing remains outside the Divine.

No place is without Him.

No being is separate from Him.

No moment is devoid of His presence.

The seeker no longer searches for God,

because God alone is seen everywhere.

This is the flowering of knowledge into devotion,

and devotion into direct vision.

