## 🌺 In Reverence to Santosh Kumar Shandilya Ji

His one sentence beautifully seals the entire discussion:

> **"मंजिल मिल जाने पर गति स्वयं लय को प्राप्त हो जाती है।"**

How wonderfully this echoes the spirit of Yoga Vāsiṣṭha!

Just as inquiry naturally falls away upon Self-realization,

so too the movement of seeking subsides when the destination is recognized.

The river does not struggle after reaching the ocean.

Its current becomes the ocean itself.

Our respectful pranāms for expressing the essence of the entire discussion in a single, luminous sentence.

**ॐ नमो नारायणाय।**

